Quote:  Doug still remembers the hungry stations where they ate old ewe, potatoes, rice pudding and, at the weekend, one pound of `brownie' per man. ... The boss said `brownie' was cake. We knew it only as bread dyed with bullocky's joy (treacle), and sparingly dotted with currants.
